    <h2>SECTION A: Attempt any TWO questions.</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>Define statistics and discuss its importance in the field of computational sciences. The following are the numbers of minutes that a person had to wait for the bus to work on 20 working days : 15, 10, 2, 17, 5, 8, 3, 10, 2, 9, 5, 9, 13, 1, 10, 12, 5, 10, 8, 4. Compute mean, median, mode, standard, variance and coefficient of variation.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>The study of data collection, analysis, interpretation, presentation, and organization is the focus of the mathematical field of statistics. It offers strategies and resources for comprehending and controlling data variability, enabling well-informed, empirically supported decision-making.</p>
<p>Given Data,<br />
The waiting times (in minutes) for the bus over 20 working days are:</p>
<p>15, 10, 2, 17, 5, 8, 3, 10, 2, 9, 5, 9, 13, 1, 10, 12, 5, 10, 8, 4.</p>
<p>First, let&#8217;s arrange the data in ascending order:</p>
<p>1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 5, 5, 5, 8, 8, 9, 9, 10, 10, 10, 10, 12, 13, 15, 17.</p>
<p><strong>Mean</strong><br />
The mean is calculated by summing all the values and dividing by the number of values:</p>
<p>$$ Mean = \frac{{Σx_i}}{{n}}$$</p>
<p>$$Mean = \frac{{1+ 2+ 2+ 3+ 4+ 5+ 5+ 5+ 8+ 8+ 9+ 9+ 10+ 10+ 10+ 10+ 12+ 13+ 15+ 17}}{{20}}$$</p>
<p>$$Mean = \frac{{119}}{{20}}$$</p>
<p>$$Mean = 5.95 $$</p>
<p><strong>Median<br />
</strong>Since there are 20 values in the dataset (even), the median is the mean of the 10th and 11th values.</p>
<p>Using the data that has been ordered:<br />
10th value = 8, 11th value = 9 so,</p>
<p>$$Median = \frac{{8+9}}{{2}} = \frac{{17}}{{2}} = 8.5$$</p>
<p><strong>Mode<br />
</strong></p>
<p>The value that occurs most frequently in the dataset is called the mode.</p>
<p>Based on the data that was ordered:</p>
<p>5 and 10 occur 4 times, while 2 appears 2 times and 3, 4, 8, 9, 12, 13, 15, 17 each appear only once.</p>
<p>Thus, the modes are:<br />
<span class="base"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Modes </span></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">5</span><span class="mpunct">, </span><span class="mord">10</span></span></p>
<p><strong>Variance and Standard Deviation<br />
</strong>The average squared departure from the mean is measured by variance. The variance σ<sup>2</sup> formula is:</p>
<p>$$\sigma^2 = \frac{{\sum (x_i &#8211; \mu)^2}}{{n}}$$</p>
<p>Where <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">μ</span></span> is the mean, and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">n is the number of data points.</span></span></p>
<div class="table_wrapper" style="overflow-x:auto;"><table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center;">x</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center;">(x &#8211; mean)<sup>2</sup></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
